      <h3>Children learn the world <span class="it">by playing it first.</span></h3>

      <div class="body">
        <p><span class="dropcap">B</span>efore a child learns the price of bread, she weighs a felt loaf in a wooden scale. Before he understands a farm, he sleeps the calves in the shed. Dramatic Play is the toolkit for that prior learning. A farmyard with a real working tractor. A classroom market that opens at nine. A pantry where pumpkins live in baskets and rolling pins live on hooks. No batteries. No instructions. Just scene, prop, and the long generous space where a child practices being a person.</p>
      </div>

